			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- How does the MMC3 IRQ counter clock 241 times in a frame?</div><br />240 rendered scanlines + 1 "pre-render" scanline (scanline -1)<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">- If you consider the sprites, does the IRQ clock occur during the sprite evaluation or during the rendering?</div><br /><br />It occurs during the CHR fetch.  The CHR fetch is what triggers the A12 change, and thus is what triggers the IRQ counter.  This is normally on dot 260 (4 PPU cycles after the last pixel of the scanline is rendered) -- but it can change if the sprite CHR settings are changed.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">- Could someone clarify about the scanline after 20 lines of VBlank, </div><br /><br />The pre-render scanline (scanline -1... the one immediately after VBlank) does <em>everything</em> that the normal rendered scanlines do, including all CHR/NT fetches, sprite evaluations, PPU address updates, etc.  The <em>only</em> differences between the pre-render scanline and regular rendered scanlines are:<br /><br />1)  No pixels are output for the pre-render scanline (but all fetches still take place!)<br /><br />2)  The scroll is updated (loopy_v = loopy_t) on dot ?304? of the pre-render scanline, but is not updated on any of the normal rendered scanlines.<br /><br />Those two things aside... the prerender scanline behaves just like any other rendered scanline.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">plus the dummy scanline after 240 visible lines?</div><br /><br />As far as I know, the PPU is completely inactive for that scanline, so you can treat it just as if it were part of VBlank.<br /><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Anyway, perhaps I'm not being clear..? Sprites are evaluated during the pre-scanline (-1) *and* in the dummy scanline (240)?</div>
<br />
<br />Yes.</div>

