						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Heck, one more thing: you mentioned previously about a latency of 13 CPU (?) cycles between A12 rises "in your emu". Do you confirm it?</div><br /><br />No.  There is no such latency.  I may have added that to an old version of my emu because I misunderstood overall IRQ behavior.  But anyway -- you don't have to add any latency on MMC3.<br /><br />Remember you can always use blargg's MMC3 test ROMs to fine tune your timing.  Between that, and some of the trickier MMC3 games (The Incredible Crash Test Dummies comes to mind), you should be able to tweak things so they're timed right.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Plus, since I use a CHR cache system, there's no problem if I rely on PPU cycle timing for A12 rises, like (ppucycle&amp;7)-4 for CHR/Nam fetches..? ppucycle=0 up to 340.</div>
<br />
<br />PPU cycle resolution should be good.
<br />
<br />As with any IRQ, you should be able to predict when it's going to happen before it actually happens.  This gets trickier with 8x16 sprites, though, as they can fetch CHR from either pattern table.. so whether or not A12 rises may depend on which sprites are found to be inrange on a given scanline.</div>

