				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Wed Nov 10, 2004 6:47 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 1670
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- 13 dots means 1,0,1 in A12 rises. This way, the IRQ is clocked twice (?).</div><br /><br />As far as I know... yes.  1,0,1 would clock twice, but 1,1,0 would only clock once.<br /><br />I would love to have confirmation on that though.  I just remember hearing that "through the grapevine" and I don't know if it's ever actually been tested.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> Plus, according to BT's doc, the sprite CHR fetch occurs after cycle 258, and you mentioned "dot" (I use "PPU scanline cycle") 260.</div><br /><br />You must be misreading BT's doc.  Nowhere I could find does it say the CHR fetch happens on 258.  Could you paste where it says that?<br /><br />In any event... The first 256 cycles (0-255) are BG NT/Attribute/CHR fetches.  There are 32 tiles, each tile taking 4 fetches, and each fetch taking 2 cycles.  32 * 2 * 4 = 256.  This means the fetches for the first sprite occurs between cycles 256-263.  Just like with the BG, sprites have 4 fetches, each fetch taking 2 cycles each.  The first two fetches are BG/Attribute bytes (from ppu $2xxx -- where A12 is low).  These fetches are discarded and unused -- but they take 4 cycles total, meaning the first CHR fetch is on cycle 260 (256 + 4).<br /><br />BT's doc confirms this:<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Memory fetch phase 129 thru 160<br />-------------------------------<br />1. Garbage name table byte<br />2. Garbage name table byte<br />3. Pattern table bitmap #0 for applicable object (for next scanline)<br />4. Pattern table bitmap #1 for applicable object (for next scanline)<br /></div><br /><br />"memory fetch phase 129" is cycle 256 (there were 128 fetch phases before it, each 2 cycles long).  And the Pattern table bitmap (CHR) is the 3rd fetch here (+ 4 cycles).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">- Does the sprite CHR fetch occur when sprites are disabled?</div>
<br />
<br />Yes.  As long as the PPU is "on" (as long as either sprites <em>or</em> BG are enabled).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

