					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Ahh... so I'm not crazy. The sprite overflow test fails when the sprites are evaluated during the pre-rendered scanline. Well, here's what the wiki says:
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">During all <strong>visible</strong> scanlines, the PPU scans through OAM to determine which sprites to render on the next scanline.</div>
<br />
<br />So, the sprites are NOT evaluated during the dummy scanline. I don't know about the MMC3 IRQ risings, though... I was very lazy during past days. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /></div>

